# How the Web Works (Cybersecurity View)

## Flow
Browser -> DNS -> TCP -> HTTP/HTTPS -> Server -> Database -> Server -> Browser

## DNS
Resolves domain names to IP addresses

## TCP
Established connection using 3-way handshake (SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK)

## HTTP/HTTPS
Protocol for communication between client and server
- HTTP = not secure (port 80)
- HTTPS = encrypted (port 443)

## Server
Processes requests and returns responses

## Database (SQL)
Used to store and retrieve data

## Key Insight
User input flows through web applications and interacts with databases. If not handled properly, this can lead to vulnerabilities like SQL Injection.

## Cybersecurity Relevance
- Nmap idenfities open ports (80, 443)
- Wireshark captures DNS, TCP, and HTTP traffic
- SQL Injection targets database queries
